CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 12, 1955, pg. 27, reads: "Oriental Tea - Sahara Court 9, Daughters of Isis, Prince Hall Affiliation, held its fourth annual Oriental Tea on Sunday, Feb. 27, at the Centre Avenue YWCA.  Imperial Commandress Ercelle H. Moore of Buffalo, N.Y., seated on the far right, was the principal speaker and honored guest.  Seated on the far left is Illustrious Commander Cora M. Finch of the Pittsburgh group.  Standing, left to right, are Daughters Alberta Finch, Natalie Greene, Leafie White, Imperial Deputy of the Oasis; Fannie Maynor, Marcella Young, Mabel Griffin, Eula Scales, Gertrude Russell, Ora D. Highsmith, chairman; Virginia Valentine, Hazel Roberts, Cora Moon, Lavenia King, Mattie Blackwell, Catherine Gibson and Agnes Barber. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Sahara Court 9, Daughters of Isis members, from left, seated: Cora M. Finch and Ercelle H. Moore; standing: Alberta Finch, Natalie Greene, Leafie White, Fannie Maynor, Marcella Young, Mabel Griffin, Eula Scales, Gertrude Russell, Ora D. Highsmith, Virginia Valentine, Hazel Roberts, Cora Moon, Lavenia King, Mattie Blackwell, Catherine Gibson and Agnes Barber, posed in Centre Avenue YWCA for fourth annual Oriental Tea, another version
